# Calligraphic Artist Portfolio — Cursor Rules

## 1. Project Scope

- **Product**: Luxury artist portfolio & gallery website.
- **Artist**: Calligraphic artist.
- **Content**: Artworks, Gallery, Artist identity, high-end visual storytelling.
- **Style**: Luxury, minimal, editorial, artistic — calm but powerful, museum/gallery feel.

---

## 2. Tech Stack (STRICT)

| Allowed | Forbidden |
|--------|-----------|
| **Tailwind CSS only** for styling | No CSS files (except Tailwind entry) |
| **GSAP** for animations (scroll-based, subtle, premium) | No inline styles |
| **JSX** (not TSX) | — |
| **Fully responsive** (mobile-first → ultra-wide) | — |

---

## 3. Design & Animation

- **Visual**: Luxury, museum/gallery/editorial; calm but powerful.
- **Animations**: GSAP only. Subtle entrances, smooth scroll reveals. No over-animation.
- **Typography**: Clear, elegant hierarchy.

---

## 4. Tailwind Theme (MANDATORY)

Theme lives in Tailwind (e.g. `@theme` in CSS or `theme/tailwindTheme.js`). Use these as **Tailwind variables only**:

- `--color-primary`: #E6E6E6
- `--color-secondary`: #C5A880
- `--color-tertiary`: #532E1C
- `--color-quaternary`: #0F0F0F

**Rules**: No hardcoded hex/rgb anywhere. Always use theme classes (e.g. `bg-primary`, `text-tertiary`). Use contrast carefully for luxury feel.

---

## 5. Component Architecture (VERY IMPORTANT)

- Everything **reusable**; no duplicated JSX or repeated layout logic.
- All UI **data-driven**: arrays/objects → `.map()`.
- **Examples**: Gallery images → array; Artworks → array; Sections → array; Navigation → array.
- No hardcoded repeated blocks; components render from data only.

---

## 6. Dynamic Content

- **Source**: `data/*.js` (e.g. `artworks.js`, `gallery.js`, `navigation.js`).
- Components render using **`.map()` only** over these data structures.
- No hardcoded repeated UI.

---

